text: Stockton is a city in northern California. It is located on the San Joaquin River in the northern San Joaquin Valley. In 2020, it had a population of 320,804. Stockton is the 11th largest city in California and the 60th most populous city in the United States. In 2012, the city went bankrupt. The city was no longer bankrupt in February 2015. == References == Category:County seats in California Category:Cities in California Category:Settlements in San Joaquin County, California
